    "updated_at": "2024-11-21T14:05:25Z",
    "body": "I wanted to indicate when a venv is not in place, but maybe should be. Here's what worked for me:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[custom.novenv]\r\ndescription = \"show indicator when venv is missing\"\r\ncommand = \"\"\"\r\nprint \"no-venv\"\r\n\"\"\"\r\nwhen = '''[[ -f \"requirements.txt\" || -f \"pyproject.toml\" || -f \"poetry.lock\" || -f \"Pipfile\" ]] && [[ -z \"$VIRTUAL_ENV\" ]]'''\r\nformat = '[$output ](red)'\r\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
